cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.MM

This paper analyzes the design of news headlines in online media corporations, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract features related to sentiment polarity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and information retrieval. Additionally, the paper also involves the analysis of large datasets, which could fit into cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of sentiment analysis could also be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.MM (Multimedia), as it involves the study of how people consume news and the use of multimedia elements to attract clicks.
